This paper describes a system that uses ConceptNet, an open knowledge graph, to classify text based on discriminative attributes. This involves natural language processing (NLP) techniques, which are commonly used in the field of computational linguistics (cs.CL). The system also uses machine learning techniques, such as linear classifiers, which are commonly used in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also discusses the use of semantically-informed features, which could fall under the category of information retrieval (cs.IR) or semantic information (cs.SI).
